Despite the huge outcry from local Telkom customers about their faulty ADSL lines, Telkom on Wednesday reported there is &ldquo;no major network problem&rdquo; in the Pietermaritzburg area.Telkom spokesperson Gugulethu Maqetuka said despite there being no major network problems, they were following up on a number of individual cases that may involve cable or overhead line faults.&ldquo;Our teams are busy undertaking repairs on the affected lines and plan to restore the services as soon as possible.&ldquo;We take this opportunity to apologise to our customers who are impacted by this,&rdquo; said Maqetuka.Customers were encouraged to continue to report faulty lines.